TY  - JOUR
AU  - Leininger, Wolfgang
T1  - Rawls' Maximin Criterion and Time-Consistency: Further Results
PY  - 1985
Y1  - 1985/07/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297667
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 52
IS  - 3
SP  - 505
EP  - 513
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The paper is concerned with the implications of a maximin welfare function for an intertemporal society which has a nonlinear technology at its disposal, but holds conflicting preferences over time. The complete solution given shows that time-consistency and optimality of plans may or may not be compatible. The time-consistent case is generalized to a very wide class of models. This leads to the partial invalidation of a result stated in the earlier literature on the subject.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297667
ER  - 



