T1  - Price Setting Supergames with Capacity Constraints
PY  - 1985
Y1  - 1985/07/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297659
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 52
IS  - 3
SP  - 371
EP  - 382
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper examines the role of industry capacity in enforcing collusion in the context of repeated games. For a fixed capacity per firm it is shown that changes in the number of firms have a non-monotone effect on the best enforceable cartel price. This is due to the fact that while an additional firm lowers the share that each of the other firms enjoys at the collusive price it also increases the losses to each firm should the cartel fail.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297659
ER  - 



