T1  - Equilibrium Price Distributions
PY  - 1985
Y1  - 1985/07/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297666
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 52
IS  - 3
SP  - 487
EP  - 504
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Equilibrium price distributions (for a homogeneous product) consistent with individual incentives are investigated. They arise in informationally imperfect markets in which the only primitive datum is the distribution of search costs. It is shown that single, multi- and continuous price distributions are all viable long-run phenomena depending on the nature of search costs. A method for computing equilibrium price distributions is also provided.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297666
ER  - 



